verbose_text: The results indicate that baicalin stimulates the expression of Wnt3a, Wnt5a, frizzled 7 and disheveled 2 whilst inhibiting the Axin / casein kinase 1alpha/adenomatous polyposis coli / glycogen synthase kinase 3beta degradation complex, leading to accumulation of beta-catenin and activation of Wnt / beta-catenin signaling.
